   <concept id="DFARS_233.215" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2">
      <title>
         <ph props="autonumber">233.215</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
      <conbody>
         <p>Use Alternate I of the clause at FAR 52.233-1, Disputes,
when—</p>
         <p outputclass="List2">(1) The acquisition is for—</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(i) Aircraft</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(ii) Spacecraft and launch vehicles</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(iii) Naval vessels</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(iv) Missile systems</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(v) Tracked combat vehicles</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(vi) Related electronic systems;</p>
         <p outputclass="List2">(2) The contracting officer determines
that continued performance is—</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(i) Vital to the national security, or</p>
         <p outputclass="List3">(ii) Vital to the public health and welfare;
or</p>
         <p outputclass="List2">(3) The head of the contracting activity
determines that continued performance is necessary pending resolution
of any claim that might arise under or be related to the contract.</p>
      </conbody>
